About_me: Joined Shell in September 2015 as a Civil & Structural Engineer. I am part of the Civil, Structural and Offshore (CSO) team in Rijswijk, Netherlands and provide technical services to projects and assets within EMEA. I primarily support the Integrated Gas (IG) superbucket, providing Civil input on Regas opportunities. I'm originally from Dorset in the United Kingdom and later moved to London. There I Studied Civil & Environmental Engineering (MEng) at Imperial College and completed a thesis on the statistics of extreme waves in wind-driven seas. During my degree I was successful in an Assessed Internship with Shell, leading to my graduate role. The topic of my internship was LNG Import Terminal Concepts and the decision process for Identify – Select on these opportunities.
